132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 219
H.P. 142 House of Representatives, January 21, 2025
An Act to Limit Hypodermic Apparatus Exchange Programs to a
One-for-one Exchange
Received by the Clerk of the House on January 16, 2025. Referred to the Committee on
Health and Human Services pursuant to Joint Rule 308.2 and ordered printed.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative MASTRACCIO of Sanford.
Cosponsored by Representative: FREDERICKS of Sanford, Senator: HARRINGTON of York.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 22 MRSA §1341, sub-§1, ¶A, as amended by PL 2021, c. 545, §1, is further
3 amended to read:
4 A. The Maine Center for Disease Control and Prevention may shall limit the number
5 of hypodermic apparatuses provided by the certified hypodermic apparatus exchange
6 programs to participants to one hypodermic apparatus per participant for each
7 hypodermic apparatus exchanged by that participant.
8 SUMMARY
99 This bill limits the number of hypodermic apparatuses that may be exchanged by a
1100 hypodermic apparatus exchange program certified by the Maine Center for Disease Control
1111 and Prevention to one per participant for each one exchanged by that participant.
